# Template — copy to `.env.production` / `.env.staging` (or export in your shell).
#
# `rig deploy --stage <stage>` loads `.env.<stage>` (then `.env.local`, then
# `.env`) into the deploy env. Only names declared in the manifest's `secrets:`
# are sent to the deploy. Real values belong in `.env.local` (gitignored) or
# your shell, which always win. `.env.example` itself is never loaded.

# When set, publishing a post requires this token. Use a DIFFERENT value per
# stage so the production app and a bluegreen staging sibling don't share it.
ADMIN_TOKEN=
